WEBVTT

00:00.011 --> 00:02.350
Hey! This is your travel host, Naomi.

00:02.550 --> 00:05.700
I'd like to give you a tour of the top 10 attractions of Paris.

00:05.850 --> 00:07.900
Number 10: Hotel de Ville.

00:07.950 --> 00:14.150
This grand, Neo-Renaissance style landmark built centuries ago is home of the city administration.

00:14.350 --> 00:17.000
Number 9: Place de la Concorde.

00:17.250 --> 00:18.950
The largest square in Paris.

00:19.000 --> 00:24.100
It has a 3000-year-old Egyptian obelisk and is particularly beautiful at night.

00:24.200 --> 00:26.400
Number 8: The Pompidou Center.

00:26.500 --> 00:30.800
A colorfully creative, modern building housing a vast collection of modern art.

00:30.900 --> 00:33.250
Number 7: Arc de Triomphe.

00:33.550 --> 00:38.400
Built in the early 1800s by Napoleon, the Arc is a symbol of national pride.

00:38.500 --> 00:41.400
At the top, you'll find fantastic views of Paris.

00:41.500 --> 00:43.900
Number 6 is the Seine boat cruise.

00:44.000 --> 00:46.950
It's affordable, convenient, and in a short period of time,...

00:47.050 --> 00:49.500
...you can see many major landmarks of the city.

00:49.550 --> 00:51.850
Number 5: Versailles Palace.

00:51.950 --> 00:56.250
A royal chateau just outside of Paris has grand architectures,...

00:56.300 --> 00:59.000
...700 rooms, and beautiful gardens.

00:59.050 --> 01:00.850
Number 4: Notre Dame.

01:01.000 --> 01:05.750
One of the most recognized symbols in the world and over 750 years old,...

01:05.850 --> 01:09.050
...Notre Dame has incredibly detailed Gothic architecture.

01:09.250 --> 01:11.100
Number 3: Sacre-Coeur.

01:11.250 --> 01:14.300
This Byzantine style, stunning white church,...

01:14.400 --> 01:18.900
...despised by intellectuals when it was built, is a must-see for Paris visitors.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.350
Number 2: The Louvre Museum.

01:21.500 --> 01:24.150
Perhaps the world's most famous museum,...

01:24.200 --> 01:29.300
...it hosts thousands of pieces of great art including Leonardo Da Vinci's Mona Lisa.

01:29.650 --> 01:32.000
And number 1 is the Eiffel Tower.

01:32.150 --> 01:35.900
Amongst the most recognizable and visited monuments in the world,...

01:36.000 --> 01:39.350
...everyone must experience the Eiffel Tower in their lifetime.

01:41.050 --> 01:44.000
Keep watching our travel series. Ciao!

